To build a program using the CFITSIO dll:

	Include the header files fitsio.h and longnam.h in your source code

	Generate an import library (.lib) file from the supplied CFITSIO
	module definition (cfitsio.def) file

	Link your program using the .lib file

For example, to build the test program using Borland C++, execute these two
commands:

	implib cfitsio.lib cfitsio.def
	bcc32 -f testprog.c cfitsio.lib

To build the test program using Microsoft Visual C++, execute these two
commands:

	lib/def:cfitsio.def
	cl testprog.c cfitsio.lib
